Magic Recipe
Android App To Find Recipes with Ingredients ,
By Khizar Heyat Khan
Description
This Android application allows users to enter ingredients they have in their kitchen to get customized recipe results using the recipepuppy API.

Setup/Installation Requirements
You will need the following programs installed on your computer.

Android Studio
Java JDK 8+
Android SDK

To Run
In a terminal window, navigate to ~/AndroidStudioProjects
Run git clone https://github.com/khankhizar/MagicRecipe.git
Navigate to ~/AndroidStudioProjects/MagicRecipe
Run on either an emulator or an Android OS Device connected to a computer
To set up an emulator
Select Run > Run 'app'
Click 'Create New Emulator'
Select the device you would like to emulate (Recommended: Nexus 6)
Select the API level you would like to run - click 'Download' if not available (Recommended: Marshmallow - ABI: x86)
Select configuration settings for emulator
Click 'Finish' and allow Emulator to run

Technologies Used
Java, Android Studio, testing with Robolectric and Espresso,  recipepuppy API
